cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is about cross-language text summarization, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a compressive framework, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also uses deep learning models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Furthermore, the paper evaluates the proposed method using automatic evaluation metrics, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
